# OpenCode Configuration for Alpha Project

## Project Context
Alpha is a business directory platform with:
- Backend: Spring Boot 3.2 + Kotlin + PostgreSQL (port 3000)
- Frontend: React + Vite (port 5173)
- Database: PostgreSQL running on port 5433

## Development Workflow
1. Always kill existing processes before starting (use PowerShell):
   - Kill all node processes: `powershell -Command "Get-Process node* -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force"`
   - Kill processes using port 5173: `powershell -Command "Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 5173 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force }"`
   - Kill processes using port 3000: `powershell -Command "Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 3000 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force }"`
   - Verify: `timeout /t 2 /nobreak >nul && powershell -Command "if (Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 5173 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue) { Write-Host 'WARNING: Port 5173 still in use' -ForegroundColor Yellow }" && powershell -Command "if (Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 3000 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue) { Write-Host 'WARNING: Port 3000 still in use' -ForegroundColor Yellow }" && powershell -Command "if (Get-Process node* -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue) { Write-Host 'WARNING: Node processes still running' -ForegroundColor Yellow }"`
2. Backend runs on port 3000: `cd backend && ./gradlew bootRun`
3. Frontend runs on port 5173: `cd frontend/web && npm run dev`
4. Database runs on port 5433 (PostgreSQL)

## Code Conventions
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Follow existing patterns in codebase
- Fix root causes, not symptoms
- Never use mock data when real API/database is available
- Handle CORS properly (no Vite proxy)
- Use PowerShell for all shell commands on Windows (no bash)

## Testing Requirements
- Run tests after significant changes
- Backend: `cd backend && ./gradlew test`
- Frontend: `cd frontend/web && npm run test`
- Check TypeScript: `cd frontend/web && ./node_modules/.bin/tsc --noEmit`

## Environment
- Frontend .env in `frontend/web/.env`
- Backend .env in `backend/.env`
- CORS_ORIGIN includes http://localhost:5173 and http://localhost:5179
- Database connection: postgresql://alpha_user:alpha_password@localhost:5433/alpha
- Frontend uses VITE_API_URL, backend uses DATABASE_URL

## Common Tasks
- Database migrations: `cd backend && ./gradlew flywayMigrate`
- Build backend: `cd backend && ./gradlew build`
- Run backend: `cd backend && ./gradlew bootRun`
- Build frontend: `cd frontend/web && npm run build`
- Install frontend dependencies: `cd frontend/web && npm install --legacy-peer-deps`
- Lint frontend: `cd frontend/web && npm run lint`
- Type check frontend: `cd frontend/web && ./node_modules/.bin/tsc --noEmit`

## Important Notes
- ALL shell commands must use PowerShell syntax on Windows
- Do NOT use bash-specific syntax (&&, ||, etc.) - use PowerShell equivalents
- Always use PowerShell for process management and port checking
- Frontend package.json located at `frontend/web/package.json`, not root
- Shared package located at `frontend/shared/`